  "texts": [
    "Second, the amount of time required to respond to an item will depend on the judgment in question; for single words, 5 s is reasonable (e.g., the average response time in Winter et al., 2023 was under 5 s), but a longer sentence or passage will naturally take longer to read and produce a judgment about.",
    "Additionally, a single judgment per item is unusual.",
    "For example, Winter et al. (2023) and Trott & Bergen (2022) collected at least ten judgments per item.",
    "The number required will depend on the relative precision of any given human judgment.",
    "Recall that for a number of datasets, GPT-4's correlation with the human mean was higher than the average inter-annotator agreement (see Fig. 1)."
  ],
